OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mainly dry, bright morning.
OL,6,FTurning overcast with outbreaks of
OL,7,Frain during the afternoon, some of
OL,8,Fwhich may be heavy. Freshening winds,
OL,9,Foccasionally strong later in the north.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA cloudy, damp evening with
OL,12,Foccasionally heavy rain spreading
OL,13,Feastwards. Turning drier through the
OL,14,Frest of the night with some clearer
OL,15,Fspells developing. Blustery winds,
OL,16,Fstrong at times.
OL,17,
OL,18,CThursday:FA bright, breezy day with
OL,19,Fsome sunny intervals. Most places will
OL,20,Fbe dry, but the odd light shower in
OL,21,Fthe north can't be ruled out.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
